        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-8"><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How often do fire extinguishers need to be inspected in Madison, WI?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">In Madison, WI, fire extinguishers require monthly visual inspections (by building staff), annual professional inspections by a licensed technician, 6-year internal examinations, and 12-year hydrostatic testing per NFPA 10 and the Wisconsin Commercial Building Code / IFC.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How much does a fire extinguisher inspection cost in Madison, WI?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Annual inspections in the Madison metro typically cost $14–$36 per unit. 6-year internal examinations run $24–$52 per unit. 12-year hydrostatic tests cost $30–$65 per unit. Volume discounts apply for properties with 20+ extinguishers.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Who can inspect fire extinguishers in Madison, WI?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Monthly visual checks can be done by trained building staff. Annual, 6-year, and 12-year service must be performed by a licensed fire protection technician. Wisconsin requires fire extinguisher service contractors to hold appropriate credentials under Wisconsin state law, administered by the Wisconsin DSPS (608-266-2112). Verify your service provider's credentials before scheduling annual inspections.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">What are the penalties for fire extinguisher violations in Madison?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">The Madison Fire Department issues violation notices with correction periods for fire extinguisher deficiencies. Uncorrected violations carry escalating fines. Serious life-safety deficiencies face accelerated enforcement action.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Does Madison require fire extinguishers in all commercial buildings?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Yes. The Wisconsin Commercial Building Code / IFC requires portable fire extinguishers in all commercial, industrial, and multi-family residential buildings in Madison. Type, size, and placement depend on occupancy classification and hazard level per NFPA 10.</p></div></div>
